paper thickness
Here, we show an example of how the marker Width can be calculated
for a tool with a 8.35 [mm] diameter. For a different tool size you can use the same logic:
To get a "neon-looking" green we recommend you to buy green sticker paper,
and then you can print on the green paper instead of white paper.
If you print on green paper you should remove the green color from the marker,
and keep only the black-and-white regions:
Step 1 - Create an Inkscape page, (File > New)
Step 2 - Adjust document size, here we have an A4 for example (File > Document Properties...)
Step 3 - Add markers to that page
Step 5 - Save Inkscape file (File > Save)
Step 4 - Copy that marker multiple times on the page, so that you print many markers in once
Step 6 - Save PDF file for printing (File > Save as.... > .PDF > Save)
Inkscape
(a) Choose a high DPI like 2000
(b) Do not rasterize the markers
Drag the `marker.svg` file into your Inkscape page
(a) lock the Widht-to-Hight aspect ratio
(b) set Inkscape to use [mm]
(c) change `W` for the appropriate Width:
(d) adjust the background color to the printing paper color
